# Agent approval harness

## Run mode (user IDE)

User runs Cursor in **Auto-review** — never **Run Everything** for this project.

## MUST ask (approval card) before

- `sudo`, `ssh`, `scp`, `rsync` to VPS or any remote host
- `git push`, force git operations, production deploy scripts
- Reading or printing credential files (`credentials.txt`, `.env`, JWT keys)
- Installing system packages (`apt`, `snap`) unless user asked in the same message
- Changing nginx, systemd, or Docker on VPS

## Safe without extra prompt (still subject to Cursor classifier)

- `go test`, `go vet`, `golangci-lint`, local `git diff` / `git status`
- Editing files in this repo per user request

## Sudo on Linux

Agent terminals are non-interactive. User enables **Legacy Terminal Tool** in Cursor Settings for password prompts when approving a command.

Prefer **scoped** `NOPASSWD` in `/etc/sudoers.d/cursor-agent` — never `NOPASSWD: ALL`.
